<DOCNO> XIE19980911.0001 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Killed as C-130 Hits Another in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Four crewmen were killed
and five others injured when a Pakistan Air Force C-130 aircraft
went out of control and hit a parked C-130 at the Chaklala Air
Base, around 20 km south of here, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The C-130 Hercules aircraft was returning to the parking area
after a routine ground check, but it went out of control when a
fire broke out in its brake system, said officials with the PAF
Public Relations.
</P>
<P>
The plane hit another C-130 parked on the tarmac and both
aircraft caught fire and sustained major damage, they said.
</P>
<P>
A thick column of smoke could be seen from miles, causing panic
among the people living in the vicinity of the air base.
</P>
<P>
Fire brigade sources said at least ten fire tenders were used
to put out the blaze which continued for some 45 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The firemen said they pulled out four badly burnt bodies while
the five injured were rushed to local hospitals. Two of the
injured were reported to be in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the incident security was tightened around
the air base and no civilian personnel were allowed to enter the
area.
</P>
<P>
The extent of the damage to the aircraft could not be
immediately be ascertained, however it is estimated to be severe.
</P>
<P>
A board of inquiry has been ordered to investigate into the
incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980911.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meeting on Gender Mainstreaming in South Asia to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 10 (Xinhua) -- A two-day meeting on gender
mainstreaming in the South Asian region will begin here Friday,
the U.N. Development Fund for Women (UNIFEM) said in a press
release Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will draw together secretaries and senior officials
of the women affairs ministries, members of national planning
commissions, representatives of key NGOs and activists from the
seven member countries of the South Asian Association for Regional
Cooperation -- Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Nepal,
Pakistan and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, organized jointly by the Nepali government and
UNIFEM, aims to build on existing activities on gender
mainstreaming and to evolve a strategy and time frame for a
regional intervention for engendering the plan process, UNIFEM
said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the meeting will focus on the gender mainstreaming
of national development plans, and countries in the region will
share their current experiences of building gender issues into
development plans.
</P>
<P>
All participating states at the Fourth World Conference on
Women in Beijing in September 1995 agreed that gender
mainstreaming was one of the fundamental strategies to achieve
equality between women and men, and that an active and visible
policy toward it would be promoted.
</P>
<P>
Gender mainstreaming refers to a strategy for making gender
considerations an integral dimension in the design,
implementation, monitoring and evaluation of policies and programs
in all political, economic and societal spheres so that inequality
is not perpetuated and women and men can benefit equally, UNIFEM
said.
</P>
<P>
But the second South Asian regional meeting on women issues
which ended here Thursday noted that there is a lack of proper
mainstreaming of gender consideration across sectors in the
region, where gender continues to be seen as a "women's issue" and
the responsibility of the women affairs ministries only.
</P>
<P>
The meeting on gender mainstreaming will build on the
just-concluded regional meeting, which reached consensus on major
achievements, critical gaps and serious concerns that have
characterized the SAARC countries since the Beijing conference,
UNIFEM added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
