-- A Howard government attempt to brand Labor a big spender
backfired Wednesday, when Treasurer Peter Costello conceded that
his own figures put the cost of the Coalition's election promises
on a par with the Australian Labor Party's 18 billion Australian
dollars (10.5 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Age:
</P>
<P>
-- Australia must reduce its 222 billion Australian dollars
(129.8 billion U.S. dollars) overseas debt or risk falling victim
to the kind of shifts in international market sentiment and
capital flows that ignited the Asian financial crisis, Moody's
Investors Services warned Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review:
</P>
<P>
-- More than half of Australia's leading companies use video
surveillance to monitor their workers and the general public,
according to a Price Waterhouse Coopers survey released Wednesday.
 
