<HEADLINE> South African President Mandela to Visit Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Jean Chretien
announced Thursday that the President of South Africa Nelson
Mandela will make a state visit to Canada on September 24 and 25,
upon the invitation of the Governor General Romeo LeBlanc.
</P>
<P>
"Canada is honored by President Mandela's visit," said the
Canadian Prime Minister in a release. "He is a living symbol of
the two historic movements that have defined the 20th century:
equality and democracy. His time here will give Canadians a chance
to applaud his extraordinary and inspirational role in South
Afria's peaceful transition from apartheid to democracy."
</P>
<P>
"I also look forward to discussing new opportunities for
expanding out bilateral relationship with the President," added
the Prime Minister.
</P>
<P>
President Mandela will meet with the Governor General, Prime
Minister Chretien, Foreign Affairs Minister Lloyd Axworthy and
International Trade Minister Sergio Marchi in Ottawa on September
24.
</P>
<P>
In the morning of September 25, President Mandela will attend
an event at the Toronto Skydome to launch the Canadian Friends of
the Nelson Mandela Children's Fund. Later in the day, he will
participate in the Canada-South Africa Business Summit sponsored
by the High Commission for South Africa in Canada and the Canadian
Department of Foreign Affairs and International Trade.
</P>
<P>
The President will be accompanied on his visit by South African
Minister of Finance Minister Trevor Manuel, South African Minister
for Health Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma, South African Minister of
Safety an Security Sidney Mufamadi and Deputy Foreign Minister
Aziz Pahad. 
</P>
