<HEADLINE> Primakov Calls on EU for Supporting Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Russia's acting Foreign
Minister Yevgeny Primakov on Thursday confirmed that "Russia is
loyal to the course of economic and political reform", according
to the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
This remark voiced by Primakov, who was just nominated by the
Russian president as prime minister, when meeting with the
representatives of the European Union delegation.
</P>
<P>
After the 45-minute meeting, head of the EU delegation Austrian
diplomat Peter Hoenchvelner told the press that Primakov "had made
no special requests, except one: to support Russia in its
reforms."
</P>
<P>
"The EU will react positively" to the request, the Austrian
diplomat said and expressed hope that the foreign ministers of
Australia, Britain and Germany would soon come to Moscow.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the EU delegation brought to Moscow a
statement approved by EU foreign ministers in Salzburg last
Saturday. The statement expresses the solidarity of EU with Russia
"at a critical time and confidence that Russia would overcome its
difficulties."
</P>
<P>
Hoenchvelner said that today's meeting convinced them that "our
hopes are justified and reforms in Russia will continue".
</P>
<P>
Russian acting Deputy Foreign Minister Alexander Avdeyev told
the press that at the meeting Primakov "reaffirmed Russia's
determination to broaden strategic partnership with the European
Union."
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting was focused on the problems, values and
priorities which will be discussed during meeting of Russian
President Boris Yeltsin with the EU leaders in October.
</P>
<P>
The representatives also discussed ways of making the EU
support for Russia more effective in this dramatic period.
</P>
<P>
The EU is interested in the promotion of reform in Russia and
will support the programs which the Russian people, parliament and
government will chose, Avdeyev said.
</P>
<P>
In his view, the EU is ready to give Russia moral and other
support at this crucial period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
