<HEADLINE> UK to Launch Campaigns on Promoting Image Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Britain announced Thursday it
was planning a series of public relations campaigns abroad in an
effort to promoted the country's image in some of the world's
major nations.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a London seminar on projecting a new identity for
Britain as the new millennium approaches, British Foreign Office
minister Derek Fatchett said: "We are keen to increase the profile
of Britain and challenge the beliefs and prejudices of people
about this country."
</P>
<P>
The first campaign, which was designed to herald Britain's
commercial, scientific and artistic skills, will be held in the
German city of Hannover in 2000 to coincide with the Expo world
fair.
</P>
<P>
The British minister noted that the other series are expected
to be held in China, Brazil, Poland, South Africa and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
"We chose these countries for a number of reasons -- political
development, their political importance for Britain and market
opportunities," Fatchett said. 
</P>
