<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and Israel signed
here Thursday a five-year plan of cooperation in the fields of
health and medicine aimed at strengthening the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The deal was signed by Cyprus' Health Minister Christos
Solomis and his visiting Israeli counterpart Joshua Matza after
their talks in the Health Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the signing ceremony, Matza said he was very
pleased to have concluded the agreement with Cyprus, which he
described as a "very friendly country."
</P>
<P>
