<HEADLINE> German FM: Primakov Deserves Trust </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 10 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel Thursday expressed his support of Yevgeny Primakov's
nomination as Russia's new prime minister, saying "Primakov
deserves our trust."
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the German newspaper Suedwest Presse,
Kinkel said that Primakov "could be the man who would put the
relations among executive, parliament and regions in Russia in
order".
</P>
<P>
It would contribute to a stabilization in Russia and would
restore the lost trust if Primakov's nomination was confirmed by
the Russian State Duma, the lower house of parliament, Kinkel
added.
</P>
