support Russia on the difficult path of its reform process.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Primakov could count on Germany as a close
partner.
</P>
<P>
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl has not given any comment on
Primakov's nomination so far.
</P>
<P>
According to German government spokesman Otto Hauser, Russian
President Boris Yeltsin informed Kohl of his decision on the new
prime minister nomination during their telephone talks Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin assured Kohl that the new government would pursue the
policy of reforms and would do everything to bring the country's
economic development out of danger as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's decision to submit a new prime minister candidate
averted a possible dissolution of the State Duma, which had
rejected twice the nomination of Viktor Chernomyrdin before.
</P>
