that Iran, that has established its military buildup along its
border with Afghanistan, has been prepared to launch a military
strike on Taliban's targets.
</P>
<P>
Following the grand military maneuver of the Islamic
Revolutionary Guards Corps on the northeastern border early this
month, Iran's army on Thursday also announced to launch a large
war game along the eastern border with Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The six-point foreign ministry statement said the Taliban and
Pakistan had offered assurance to Iran about the safety of Iranian
diplomats before the fall of Mazari Sharif, a town in northern
Afghanistan, to the hands of the Taliban on August 8.
</P>
<P>
Iran believed that 11 diplomats of the Iranian consulate in
Mazari Sharif and a reporter of the Iranian official news agency
IRNA were kidnaped by the Taliban and transferred to unknown place.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban is responsible to deliver the bodies of the killed
Iranian diplomats to Iran as soon as possible, the Foreign
