<HEADLINE> U.S. Considering Additional Food Aid to DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The United States is
considering the possibility of providing an additional 300,000
tons of food aid to the Democratict People's Republic of Korea
(DPRK) after reaching some agreements during last week's U.S.-DPRK
talks in New York, the State Department said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
State Department spokesman James Rubin told reporters that
Washington would make good on promised fuel oil deliveries to the
DPRK in return for Pyongyang agreeing to resume missile talks and
previous obligations to freeze its nuclear program.
</P>
<P>
