between the two government during talks last week in New York.
</P>
<P>
Rubin confirmed that the United States was considering new
humanitarian food aid to the DPRK. Other officials said the
donation would be in the area of 300,000 tons of food, but Rubin
said no decision had been made.
</P>
<P>
Rubin said the United states guaranteed the DPRK that it will
provide a promised 284,000 tons of heavy fuel oil this year and
added that the administration was confident, after talks with
Congress, that this pledge can be honored. 
