<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, September 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RAMALLAH -- The Palestinians have expressed objection to any
changes in a reported United States proposal on Israel's further
withdrawal from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
"Any attempt to fragment the American package will only
complicate matters," senior Palestinian negotiator Saeb Erekat
told reporters Wednesday night after a meeting between Palestinian
National Authority President Yasser Arafat and U.S. Mideast envoy
Dennis Ross.
</P>
<P>
Erekat stressed that the Palestinians "will not allow such
act," adding that they are still waiting for a positive Israeli
response to the U.S. plan.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has called on Israel to withdraw from a further 13
percent of the West Bank. The Palestinians have accepted the
initiative, but Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu balked
at it. (BC-Palestine-Ross-Peace Process)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Amid growing tension between Tehran and the Afghan
Taliban militia, Iran announced on Thursday to launch another
grand maneuver on the country's eastern border in the near future.
</P>
<P>
"The annual Zolfaqar military maneuver will be carried out soon
in the eastern border areas," the army's chief of staff Ali
Shahbazi announced to the official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
Shahbazi did not mention the date and place of the maneuver,
but said that the maneuver would be unprecedented in terms of its
scope and variety of operations.
</P>
<P>
He said that the order for the maneuver has been issued and the
necessary forces have been stationed in the region during the past
month. (BC-Iran-Maneuver)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The number of Palestinians supporting the peace
process and the Oslo Accords declined, said a public opinion poll
released here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The poll, conducted by the Jerusalem Media and Communication
Center (JMCC) by the end of August, said the decline in support
shown this year is a departure from the first four years of Oslo,
when the Palestinian public showed consistent support for the
Palestinian-Israeli peace process despite sudden and dramatic
political and economic changes.
</P>
<P>
The negative trend can be measured through three main
indicators of the poll: support for Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat, his faction Fatah and the peace process itself.
(BC-Palestine-Poll-Peace Process)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran stated on Thursday that the Afghan Taliban
militia and Pakistan are responsible for the killing of Iranian
diplomats in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
According to the state-run television, the Iranian Foreign
Ministry issued a statement after a Taliban spokesman announced
that the group has found the bodies of nine Iranian
diplomats missing since August 8. (BC-Iran-Statement-Diplomats)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A senior Israeli official said Thursday that an
Israeli-Palestinian deal on the West Bank redeployment is possible
as U.S. envoy Dennis Ross continues his mediation.
</P>
<P>
David Bar-Illan, media adviser to Netanyahu, said Ross'
decision to extend his stay here is a sign that positive results
could be produced. He believed that an agreement over the Israeli
redeployment could be reached during Ross' visit.
</P>
<P>
"We certainly hope so, and there is no reason we should not
(reach an agreement), particularly since Israel has agreed in
principle to consider the 13.1 percent withdrawal which is the
only requirement in the American initiative which applies to
Israel," he said. (BC-Israel-Palestine-Agreement)


10/09/98 20:3 GMT

NNNN
04:04 04:04 g # PAB
