<HEADLINE> Mandela Arrives in Mauritius for State Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PORT LOUIS (Mauritius), September 10 (Xinhua) -- South African
President Nelson Mandela arrived here Thursday afternoon for a
two-day state visit to Mauritius during which the two countries
will sign several bilateral accords on cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The visit, which will end on September 12, will "further
strengthen and enhance the already excellent relations"
between the two countries, South African Foreign Ministry said
earlier in a statement.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Mandela, and Mauritian Prime Minister Navin
Ramgoolam who paid a state visit to South Africa in February,
will hold closed-door talks and sign several bilateral agreements
on sport, arts and culture, and on cooperation in science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
Mandela is scheduled to address the National Assembly of the
Mauritian Parliament on September 12,
and will witness the signing of two private sector business
agreements between the two countries before winding up his visit
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
After the visit, the 80-year-old South African president will
attend the summit of the Southern African Development Community
(SADC) in Grand Baie, north of Mauritius, scheduled for September
13 and 14. 
