<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Former Regime Officials Released From </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia announced
Thursday that 31 of those accused of crimes under the former
Mengistu regime have been released from prison, nine of them on
bail.
</P>
<P>
Government spokeswoman Selome Taddesse said in a
statement that the freed include high-ranking army officers and
members of the Worker's Party of Ethiopia who had been in
detention for seven years.
</P>
<P>
Taddesse said: "The special prosecutor's office had considered
their cases at length and had decided that there was not enough
evidence to justify keeping them in custody to follow up their
cases."
</P>
<P>
"The release are in line with the new year gesture of
releasing prisoners," the spokeswoman added.
</P>
<P>
According to a local newspapers report, these prisoners include
Major General Bedlu Duki, former logistics commander of the
Ethiopian ground forces; Major General Techane Mesfin, former
commanding officer at headquarters of the Ethiopian Ministry of
Defense; Major General Kefelen Yibza, member of the Ethiopian
State Council and advisor on military affairs.  
