<HEADLINE> War Against Kabila Will Continue: DRC Rebel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Spokesman of the rebel
forces in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) Thursday
expressed the determination to continue their fighting against
President Laurent Kabila.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference in Midrand, north of
Johannesburg, rebel spokesman Thomas Timana accused Kabila of
being a "nepotic tribalist" who had betrayed the Alliance of
Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo/Zaire (AFDL).
</P>
<P>
The AFDL ousted Zaire president Mobutu Sese Seko in May last
year.
</P>
<P>
Timana said Kabila was only the spokesman of the AFDL when he
declared himself president of the newly-named Democratic Republic
of the Congo.
</P>
<P>
He said armed struggle was the only avenue available because
Kabila had become a dictator who jailed or dismissed anyone who
opposed him.
</P>
<P>
The rebel movement, which calls itself the Congolese Coalition
for Democracy (RCD), was formed on August 1 this year in the
eastern DRC town of Goma.
</P>
<P>
"The RCD is a structure of political and military actions
aimed at dismantling the dictatorial regime of Mr. Kabila and
establishing a democratic regime based on real popular
legitimacy," Timana said. 
</P>
