<HEADLINE> Nigeria Moves Troops to Disputed Bakassi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria says it has moved more
troops and equipment into the disputed Bakassi Penninsula, two
days after it accused Cameroon of deploying more troops there.
</P>
<P>
The British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC) quoted a defense
spokesman as saying Thursday in Lagos that there had been no
incidents yet, but Nigeria did not want to be caught off guard.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Headquarters said in a statement Tuesday that
authorities in Yaounde had as at last week deployed more troops
to the disputed areas along its border with Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon has not commented on the Nigerian accusation.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria and Cameroon have clashed for several times in the
last few years at Bakassi, a peninsula in the Guinea Gulf in West
Africa.
</P>
<P>
The dispute was filed to the International Court of Justice in
1994 but the judgement is still being expected.  
</P>
