<HEADLINE> Military Coup Attempt Foiled in Malawi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Malawi has foiled a military coup
attempt last week and arrested 15 soldiers alledgedly in connection
with the plot, Deutsche Presse-Agentur DPA reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
DAP quoted a Malawian Army spokesman as saying that the arrests
were conducted at the weekend in the capital city of Lilongwe.
</P>
<P>
A group of soldiers planned a military takeover when President
Bakili Muluzi was attending the 12th Non-Aligned Movement ending last
Thursday in Durban, South Afica.
</P>
<P>
He said the the coup attempt failed due to bad coordination and
logistics problems.
</P>
<P>
DPA also quoted the State House spokesman as saying that the
soldiers arrested for breach of army discipline.
</P>
<P>
Army sources said there has been tension in the army following the
fall of the Malawian Kwacha, the local currency. The currency dropped
3.5 percent on
August 1 and a further fall occurred later, leading sharp hike in
prices.
</P>
<P>
The continuous depreciation of the Kwacha caused mainly by Malawi's
considerable descrease in tobacco exports in the past months and its
low price in the world market. Tobacco has been Malawi's traditional
foreign exchange earner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
