<HEADLINE> Simitis: Development of Int'l Financial Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis described Friday the development in an international
financial crisis as "unpredictable", saying that his country would
take all necessary measures to deal with the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a cabinet meeting, Simitis urged the Greek
government ministers to remain alert because the financial crisis'
development would be unpredictable, the semi-official Athens News
Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
While stressing that the Greek government would not impose new
taxes, he said that the impact of an international crisis on Greek
economy now had proved that Greece was no longer a developing but
a European country.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to drachma's entry into the European exchange
rate mechanism (ERM) in March this year. Greece has said that such
a move has strengthened the country's economy and is working as a
shield against the current crisis. 
</P>
