<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Duma Confirms Primakov as Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian State Duma, the lower
house of parliament, on Friday endorsed Yevgeny Primakov's
nomination as prime minister by an overwhelmingly majority, with
315 voting for and 63 against, while 15 abstaining.
</P>
<P>
It was the third round of vote by the State Duma on premier's
nominee who needs at least 226 votes to be approved.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin nominated Primakov for premier on
Thursday after the Duma rejected Viktor Chernomyrdin twice for the
prime minister's post.
</P>
<P>
He said earlier on Friday that Russia is at a crucial moment
and that it is necessary to urgently lower prices, fill the shops
with goods again, restore the banking system, and guarantee the
safety of bank deposits.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed those issues can be solved by the new
government under the leadership of Primakov with the support of
both the president and the parliament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
