<HEADLINE> Pak FM: Govt Not to Accept CTBT Under Threat of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Foreign Minister
Sartaj Aziz Friday said the government will not accept the
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) unless economic sanctions and
pressures are removed.
</P>
<P>
"We will not accept the CTBT under an atmosphere of coercion,
the economic sanctions and pressures must be removed before we
adhere to the treaty," Aziz said in his opening statement at the
joint sitting of the parliament convened to discuss Pakistan's
position on CTBT.
</P>
<P>
He stated that Pakistan has to carefully weigh its decision
and position on the treaty banning nuclear tests as nuclear
deterrence, critical to Pakistan's self-defense, is indispensable
for the country's security.
</P>
<P>
