<HEADLINE> King Appeals To Opposition Parties to Join New Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's King Norodom
Sihanouk Friday appealed to elected parliamentarians to
participate in the new National Assembly to be convened on Sept 24.
</P>
<P>
The King extended the invitation in a letter to Prince Norodom
Ranariddh and Sam Rainsy, the leaders of the two opposition
parties of FUNCINPEC and the Sam Rainsy Party (SRP).
</P>
<P>
The King expressed the wish that the elected parliamentarians
of the two parties join the new Assembly meeting on Sept 24, the
expiration of the current Assembly.
</P>
<P>
"If you do not participate, the royal government will not
recognize you as legal assembly members and you will be deprived
of your NA privileges," the King said.
</P>
<P>
If they still refuse to join in the assembly, the king warned,
then he would not be able to protect them should they have some
problems.
</P>
<P>
The King is considered to be a pivotal figure in resolving the
political crisis in his country, although talks last weekend in
Siem Reap between the ruling Cambodian People's Party (CPP),
FUNCINPEC and the SRP failed.
</P>
<P>
King Sihanouk last week even threatened to abdicate if no
agreement is reached between the three parties this month.
</P>
<P>
A coalition is necessary because, while the CPP has a majority
in parliament, it lacks the two-thirds needed to form a government
of its own.
</P>
<P>
The two major opposition parties, which won the remainder of
parliamentary seats, have threatened to boycott parliament unless
their complaints about the election are resolved. 
</P>
