<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Communist Party
chief Le Kha Phieu said Thursday that protecting farmers' rightful
interests through state policies is a most important driving force
for agriculture's shift to commodity production, Vietnamese news
media reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the First National Conference of Successful Farmers, Party
General Secretary Le Kha Phieu said that in recent years, farmers
have raised their sense of self-reliance, unity and unanimity, and
have made important contribution to the implementation of the
party line and state policies.
</P>
<P>
Phieu stressed that agriculture has in recent years been
considered the primary front of the country's renovation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the role of agriculture and rural economy is to
ensure national food security, help stabilize socio-economic
situation, provide employment and raise income for the rural labor
force.
</P>
<P>
