<HEADLINE> Primakov Urges Duma to Ratify START-II </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian prime minister nominee
Yevgeny Primakov said Friday would ask the State Duma, the lower
house of parliament, to ratify the START-II nuclear arms reduction
treaty if the Duma confirms him in office.
</P>
<P>
"As for ratification of START-II, I will ask the Duma to ratify
it without dragging its feet," he told a parliamentary session
before a scheduled vote on whether to confirm him as prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
Primakov, currently acting foreign minister, has repeatedly
urged the opposition-dominated Duma to ratify the 1993 treaty,
which requires cutting the number of nuclear warheads deployed in
Russia and the United States from about 6,000 each to no more than
3,500 each by the year 2007.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Senate has ratified the treaty but the Russian Duma
has held back. 
</P>
