<HEADLINE> Industrial, Commercial Tax Revenue Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial and
commercial tax revenue increased in August by 3.8 percent over the
same period last year to reach 58.8 billion yuan (about 7 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sources from the State Taxation Administration said that the
growth can be attributed to increasing investment and a stable
economy.
</P>
<P>
The value-added tax and consumption tax grew by 12.3 percent
and 20.2 percent, respectively, over the same period last year,
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The total tax revenue for the whole year is expected to reach
80 billion yuan, sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
