<HEADLINE> China Strongly Condemns Killing of Iranian Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- China today expressed its
strong condemnation of the killing of Iranian diplomats in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for China's Foreign Ministry said today that the
Chinese government strongly condemns this action, because "it
seriously violates international law.
</P>
<P>
"We expressed our deep regret on the death of the Iranian
diplomats and our sympathy and solicitude to the relatives of the
victims."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that China, as a good neighbor of
Afghanistan, is highly concerned about the situation there and
hopes that all parties, proceeding from the interests of their
countries and people, cease armed conflicts at an early date.
</P>
