<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Prepares for Funding Cotton Purchases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Development
Bank of China (ADBC) has been well-prepared for providing
sufficient loans for this year's cotton purchases, sources from
the ADBC said today.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the ADBC said the bank, together with other
related departments, has estimated the amount of funds needed for
this year's cotton purchases and worked out a money-supply
schedule.
</P>
<P>
In a recent circular, the ADBC urged its branches at various
levels to take effective measures to accomplish the money-supply
work for cotton purchases.
</P>
<P>
The circular requires that newly extended loans should match
the value of the reserves of newly purchased cotton.
</P>
<P>
The ADBC also requires a closed management of loans earmarked
for purchasing cotton, demanding its branches to keep a firm
control over the volume of loans and ban any diversion of funds.
</P>
<P>
The ADBC spokesman stressed that loans for cotton purchases are
the state's policy-oriented loans and can only be used by
cotton-purchasing and reserve enterprises for that purpose.
</P>
<P>
The ADBC also requires its branches to strictly supervise and
manage the opening of accounts by cotton-purchasing enterprises to
prevent any diversion of loans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
