<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Legislative Council By-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to hold
by-election on October 29 for one seat vacated in the first
Legislative Council, a government spokesman said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The nomination for the by-election for the regional council
functional constituency will run from September 17 to 30, a
spokesman for the Registration and Electoral Office said.
</P>
<P>
Two legislators from the regional and functional constituencies
 were unseated recently, one due to Tang Siu-tong of the regional
council constituency who was declared last week not duly elected
following a court ruling that he had tied with another rival
candidate after some of his votes were declared, and the other
due to Chim Pui-chung from the functional constituency, who was
expelled from the legislature after being sentenced to a
three-year imprisonment for fraud.
</P>
<P>
The date for the by-election for the latter has not been
decided yet.
</P>
<P>
The first Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region was elected on May 24 this year. 
</P>
