<HEADLINE> House Remodeling Thriving in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- China's house remodeling
industry is entering a robust period, thanks to the rapid
improvement of the Chinese people's life quality.
</P>
<P>
An incomplete survey shows that Chinese now spend at least 50
billion yuan (about 6.02 billion U.S. dollars) on house remodeling
each year, including 12.5 billion yuan last year in Shanghai alone.
</P>
<P>
One-fifth of the families in China's major large and
medium-sized cities have already remodeled or plan to remodel
their apartments, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
It adds that nearly all the resident housing sold over the past
few years had been remodeled.
</P>
<P>
Architects attribute this emerging industry to the increase in
annual income and housing reforms which make it possible to own
private apartments.
</P>
<P>
They also pointed out some problems in the remodeling industry,
such as the use of some polluting or harmful materials and the
neglect of safety standards.
</P>
<P>
Architects have called on the media to help people who want to
remodel their houses do it safely, taking space and energy
conservation into consideration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
