<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 3.46 Percent Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks declined
271.48 points, or 3.46 percent, to end the trading session at
7,578.48 on Friday due to a fall on Wall Street and the Tokyo
market, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 5.38 billion HK dollars (689.74 million U.S.
dollars) as against the previous day's 4.288 billion HK dollars
(549.74 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The share prices in the sectors of finance, utilities,
properties, commerce and industry all registered sharp drops
ranging from 2.91 percent to 3.87 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index and H-share
index saw slight falls of 32.66 and 17.06 points respectively.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks drifted 55.49 points, or 0.7 percent, down to
finish the trade at 7,849.96 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Spurred by the Hong Kong government's package of measures to
strengthen the currency board system and curb speculators, the
market jumped 7.85 percent and 1.39 percent respectively on Monday
and Tuesday, the first two trading days of the week, when the key
Hang Seng Index once hit 8,189.25 points. 
</P>
