a cease-fire in the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
Uganda and Rwanda have been accused of backing the Tutsi
rebels in the DRC. Rwanda denied any military involvement in the
conflict while Uganda admitted it has troops in the eastern part
of Democratic Congo.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe, Angola and Namibia sent troops to prop up the
government of DRC President Laurent Kabila in mid-August, turning
the tide of the war against the rebels who were advancing to
capital Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of defense ministers is a follow-up to the
regional summit in the Zimbabwean resort town of Victoria Falls
earlier this week which ended with a commitment to seek for a
cease-fire in the DRC but without any concrete timetable.
</P>
<P>
As the war in the DRC continues to regionalize, more and more
regional and international attention has been directed to the
third largest African country.
</P>
<P>
