<HEADLINE> Bomb Blasts in Jaffna City in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A powerful bomb exploded in
the Municipality building located at Kachcheri in Jaffna city
around 11:00 a.m. Friday, a Sri Lankan Defense Ministry release
said.
</P>
<P>
Ponnuthurai Sivapalan, mayor of Jaffna, several army and police
officers and a few civilians present are suspected to have been
seriously injured, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The release did not mention if anyone died in the bomb blast,
however informed sources here said seven people including army and
police officials were killed.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred while a conference was in progress to
discuss the traffic arrangements in Jaffna city.
</P>
<P>
Rescue operations and investigations are in progress, the
release said.
</P>
