<HEADLINE> Malaysian Trade, Investment Mission to Visit U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian International
Trade and Industry Minister Rafidah Aziz will lead a trade and
investment mission to the United States from September 12 to 22,
an official statement said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The mission to New York, Chicago, Boston and Houston, would
seek joint venture opportunities in information technology and
multimedia activities, telecommunications, medical disposable
products, biotechnology and advanced materials, the statement
issued by the Ministry of International Trade and Industry said.
</P>
<P>
The mission would also find export opportunities for products
such as examination and nitrite gloves, auto accessories,
telephone equipment, household electrical and electronic products,
melamine and stainless steel housewares, food, furniture, palm oil
and services such as project management, packaging and logistics.
</P>
<P>
