<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Vietnamese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC), met here today with a delegation of the Vietnamese
Association for Peace.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is led by Vu Dinh Cu, vice-chairman of the
Vietnamese National Assembly and president of the association.
</P>
<P>
Li said that as close neighbors, China and Viet Nam experienced
similar hardships in the past, and today they are both building
socialism, developing their national economies, and safeguarding
regional stability and world peace.
</P>
<P>
These common points serve as the basis for bilateral
good-neighborliness and cooperation between the two countries, and
also constitute as the basic common interest of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Both the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the Chinese
government attach great importance to friendship with Viet Nam, Li
said, noting that since the normalization of bilateral ties,
high-level contacts have been frequent, and sound cooperation has
been carried out in various spheres, and longstanding traditional
friendship has been tightened.
</P>
<P>
The world has entered an era of high-technology, and so long as
the two countries learn from and communicate with each other,
their mutually beneficial cooperation will certainly go forward,
Li said.
</P>
<P>
Vu said he witnessed the great achievements China had scored in
socialist construction during his current visit, especially in the
scientific and technological sector, and expressed the hope that
bilateral cooperation in this regard will increase.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his solicitude to the people in China's
flooded areas, and said China's victory over the disastrous
flooding is resultant from the correct leadership of the CPC and
the full-play of the advantages of the socialist system.  
</P>
