<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Marks Flat Last Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market
marked a flat course over the past week amidst satisfactory
volume levels and several corporate announcements, a weekly market
review said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, issued by Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited, said the its All-Share Index closed Thursday
at 442.2 points, with a marginal positive deviation of 0.2 points
since last week's closing.
</P>
<P>
The review said the market was set on a shallow downtrend
since Monday, gradually shedding last Friday's gains of 2.1
points.
</P>
<P>
At current price levels the market sustains capital gains of
13.6 percent within 1998, the review said. 
</P>
