<HEADLINE> Mayor, Commander Killed in Sri Lankan Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Jaffna Mayor Ponnuthurai
Sivapalan, Commander of Jaffna city Susantha Mendis and 10 other
top army and police officers were killed in a powerful bomb
explosion in Sri Lanka's Jaffna city Friday morning, according to
official radio.
</P>
<P>
This explosion occurred at around 11:00 a.m. at the Jaffna
Municipal Council office during a conference of local politicians
and army and police officers.
</P>
<P>
The mayor succumbed to his injuries on admission to the Jaffna
hospital following the bomb attack.
</P>
<P>
A number of other civilians who were in the vicinity had been
wounded.
</P>
<P>
The circumstances of the bomb attack in Jaffna city, more than
400 kilometers from Colombo, was not immediately clear, but police
believed that Tamil rebels are responsible for the explosion,
informed sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government since 1983 for a separate state in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
