<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Football
Confederation (AFC) Friday suspended Thailand and Indonesia from
all international football matches with immediate effect,
according to the Malaysian national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
The two countries were charged with bringing "gross disrepute
to the sport and image of Asian soccer" following a bizarre group
match during last week's Tiger Cup tournament in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The AFC executive committee also ordered its Disciplinary
Board to conduct an inquiry into both teams and complete its
report by the end of next month.
</P>
<P>
AFC secretary-general Peter Velappan was quoted as saying both
nations would be suspended until AFC received the report.
</P>
<P>
The AFC executive committee, chaired by its president, Sultan
Haji Ahmad Shah, expressed concern about the action taken by both
teams in the tournament organized by the ASEAN Football
Federation(AFF). 
