<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the
Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed lower Friday on concerns
pertaining to the trading of Malaysian shares on the Central Limit
Order Book (CLOB).
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index eased
11.67 points to 368.53, the all-share Emas Index declined 3.12
points to 96.63, the Industrial Index fell 22.85 points to 710.61
and the second board index was 3.35 points down to 90.77.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 582 to 72 while 81 counters were
unchanged and 187 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover amounted to 181.876 million shares worth
268.673 million ringgit (about 70.703 million U.S. dollars) from
200.745 million shares valued at 283.528 million ringgit (about
74.612 million dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover dropped to 175.093 million shares worth
258.281 million ringgit (about 67.968 million dollars) from
192.744 million shares valued at 271.173 million ringgit (about
71.361 million dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The second board volume declined to 6.783 million shares worth
10.392 million ringgit (about 2.734 million dollars) from
Thursday's 8.001 million shares valued at 12.354 million ringgit
(about 3.251 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover, however, ballooned to 6.655 million shares
worth 9.518 million ringgit (about 2.504 million dollars) from
Thursday's 36,200 shares valued at 86,631 ringgit (about 22,797
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
