<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Pakistani Foreign Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Qian
Qichen met today with Pakistani Foreign Secretary Shamshad Ahmad,
who is here for an annual diplomatic consultation.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Qian spoke highly of China-Pakistan
relations, and expressed satisfaction with the growth of bilateral
ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is a set policy of the Chinese government to
further develop the good-neighborly and mutually beneficial
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed the belief that joint efforts will enable the
two sides to develop their ties further in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Shamshad agreed with Qian's assessment on the bilateral
relationship, saying that Pakistan and China enjoy a traditional
friendship.
</P>
<P>
He cited China as the most reliable friend of Pakistan, and
said that the Pakistani government will make concerted efforts to
build a comprehensive and cooperative partnership with China
oriented toward the 21st century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
