<HEADLINE> Pakistan Condemns Killing of Iranian Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Friday condemned
the killing of nine Iranian diplomats based in northern
Afghanistan, but said it can not accept Iran's accusation that it
was responsible for the attack.
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan cannot accept this accusation as it cannot be held
responsible or accountable for the events in a third country," a
Foreign Office spokesman said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Iran said on Thursday that it holds the Afghan Taliban militia
and Pakistan responsible for the "abhorrent" killing of Iranian
diplomats after the Taliban announced that they had recovered the
bodies of the nine Iranian diplomats in the suburbs of
Mazar-e-Sharif.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman urged the Taliban regime to "expeditiously locate
the whereabouts of the remaining two members of the Iranian
consulate" in Mazar-e-Sharif, around 300 kilometers north of
Kabul.
</P>
<P>
He said the government of Pakistan hoped that those responsible
for this act would be apprehended and punished.
</P>
<P>
He also offered condolences to the bereaved families and the
government of Iran on behalf of the government and people of
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the tension that this tragic incident has
generated between Iran and Afghanistan, the spokesman urged the
two sides to exercise restraint and resolve their differences
through peaceful negotiations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
