<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Falls in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in the
Philippines fell to 8.9 percent in July from a record high of 13.3
percent in April this year, the National Statistics Office said
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The office said the labor force was 1.5 million less than in
April this year, thus bringing the total number of the jobless
down by 1.5 million and reducing the unemployment rate.
</P>
<P>
However, this does not mean that the employment situation in
the country has improved, economists said. They added that the
labor force declined because about 758,000 more housewives,
students and disabled and retired persons chose to stay out of the
labor force.
</P>
<P>
The office added that 30.6 million persons joined the labor
force in July 1998, an increase of 439,000 people over July 1997.
Of the 439,000 people, 325,000 found jobs pushing the total
employment to 27.9 million.
</P>
<P>
Among the sectors, service saw the largest increase in
employment. It was followed by agriculture and industry, the
office said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
