<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 18.4 Million U.S. Households Participating in E-Commerce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Some 18.4 million
households in the United States make use of the Internet for their
shopping, according to a survey released Thursday.
</P>
<P>
More than 11 million households learn about products for
non-Internet purchases and 7.4 million shop for products to
purchase via online service or the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Most online American shoppers spend 20 hours or more each week,
learning about products that are then bought off-line or shopping
for products to be purchased online, said ZD Market Intelligence,
a market data provider in La Jolla, California.
</P>
<P>
The findings are based on a semi-annual survey of U.S. PC use
and users.
</P>
<P>
The study shows that Internet users and electronic-commerce
participants are similar in many ways. But the gap between these
two groups and the U.S. population as a whole widens when compared
side by side.
</P>
<P>
Online shoppers and Internet users tend to be younger, more
affluent and better-educated than the general U.S. population.
</P>
<P>
The biggest challenge in closing the e-commerce gap -- even
bigger than security, payment and standard issues -- is the fact
that more than half of households do not have PCs or Internet
access, according to the study. This fact has contributed greatly
to keeping e-commerce from reaching critical mass.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Internet penetration, bandwidth -- the
transmission capacity of a communications network -- presents
another challenge to e-commerce growth. Greater bandwidth is
crucial to creating positive consumer experience and therefore
enabling people to feel more confident participating in e-commerce
activities.
</P>
<P>
"Until there is a critical mass of PCs connected to the
Internet, e-commerce will continue to quickly outgrow the
infrastructure in place to support it," the study said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980911.0246 </DOCNO>
