<P>
This was the first such sale made by the Huafeng Peony
Horticulture Co. Ltd. through orders placed over the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The city of Luoyang has been growing peonies, a Chinese symbol
of prosperity, for more than 1,000 years, and now grows 5,000
varieties of the flower. The best peonies also come from Heze in
east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
With the aid of the Internet, the company has better marketing
prospects this year than previously, said manager Wu Jingxu.
</P>
<P>
A score of other overseas companies have also placed orders
through the Internet for 100,000 peony stems, according to Wu.
