<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Leader Leaves on U.S. Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- General Zhang Wannian,
vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission (CMC), left
here this morning on an official visit to the United States at the
invitation of U.S. Secretary of Defence William Cohen.
</P>
<P>
Zhang's party includes Lieutenant General Xiong Guangkai,
deputy chief of general staff of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA), Shi Yunsheng, commander of the PLA Navy, Li Xinliang,
commander of the PLA Beijing Garrison, and Qiao Qingchen,
deputy-commander of the PLA Air Force.
</P>
<P>
Military Sources here cited it as an important visit at the
time when Sino-US relations tuned on a good growth momentum as a
result of an exchange of successful visits by the presidents of
the two nations.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, General Zhang is expected to meet with US
governmental and military leaders and Congressmen, and confer with
Cohen on global and regional security, relations between the two
countries and their armies as well as other issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Besides talks and meetings, General Zhang and his party will
also visit units and academies of the US army, navy and air force,
which are believed to help increase mutual understanding and trust
and promote the Sino-US ties and military relations.
</P>
<P>
Upon his leaving for the U.S., General Zhang and his party were
seen off at the airport by General Fu Quanyou, member of the CMC
and chief of the PLA General Staff, and Lieutenant General Dong
Liangju, director of the CMC General Office, and other ranking
Chinese officers as well U.S. Ambassador James Ralph Sasser.
</P>
