<HEADLINE> Qinghua to Recruit Staffers from Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Qinghua University, one of
China's most prestigious universities, plans to improve
instructional quality by recruiting faculty members from the ranks
of Chinese students and scholars studying or working abroad.
</P>
<P>
The university plans to hire 100 outstanding young and
middle-aged scholars overseas over the next few years.
</P>
<P>
The new staffers will be assigned to state level research
programs and open courses for higher grades.
</P>
<P>
The university will offer new faculty members with
research funds of two million yuan, and will offer both bonuses
and housing subsidies.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua has also established a "visiting scholar program" to
attract more outstanding staffers.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 55.3 percent of Qinghua's faculty and staff are
under the age of 45. Some 647 members of the staff hold doctorate
degrees and 122 work as professors or researchers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
