<HEADLINE> 7 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- At Least seven Tamil rebels
were killed Thursday in fierce fighting in North and East Sri
Lanka between the rebels and government troops, a military
spokesman said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops Thursday continued
operations in the southeast of Mankulam town, killing at least
four Tamil rebels.
</P>
<P>
In another incident around 5:00 p.m. Thursday at Olumadu,
government troops sniped and killed two rebels.
</P>
<P>
On the same day around 1:00 p.m. at Sittandi in Batticaloa
District, a group of rebels disguised as civilians launched an
attack with small arms and grenades on a group of soldiers on
patrol.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated with small arms killing one rebel.
</P>
<P>
Subsequently the troops recovered the dead body of the rebel
and said two soldiers also were killed during the clash.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a war for a separate state in
the north and east of the country since 1983. 
</P>
