<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Fishermen Discover Fake Money Notes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Three Bangladeshi fishermen
discovered a large amount of forged money near the Zia
International Airport in the capital city on Thursday, media
reports said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The fishermen found the fake money notes, with a total face
value of 7.73 million taka (about 150,500 U.S. dollars), in their
fishing net in a lake near the airport. The counterfeit bills were
bundled in a sack in 1,758 broad sheets.
</P>
<P>
They immediately informed the policemen on duty nearby.
</P>
<P>
It was not known who made the forged money notes and why they
were thrown in the lake. The case was still under investigation.
</P>
