<HEADLINE> World Gastroenterology Congress to Be Held in Bangkok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The 15,000-member World
Gastroenterology Congress will hold its next convention in 2002 in
Bangkok, it was announced late Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Judges, representing some 75 countries, voted 53:22 in favor of
Thailand over Singapore as the venue.
</P>
<P>
Held every four years, the congress will be one of the biggest
medical conventions ever to be held here and will generate
employment along with an income of 1.5 billion baht (about 375
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The event will convene at the Bangkok International Trade and
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Medical conventions are among the most sought after in the
meetings and conventions industry owing to the high purchasing
power of participants.
</P>
<P>
Tourism Authority of Thailand chairman Jurin Laksanavisit said:
"We thank the judges of the International Gastroenterology
Association for their support. We will do everything possible to
ensure that their convention is among the best ever."
</P>
<P>
He said the decision would lift morale in the Thai tourism
industry and prove that the industry has credibility even in this
time of crisis.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of gastroenterological associations from 32
countries came to Thailand on exploratory visits before the
decision was made. The Thai government and the private sector had
spent about 18.8 million bath (450,000 dollars) on preparatory
efforts.
</P>
<P>
The last gastroenterology congress was held in Vienna earlier
this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
