<HEADLINE> IDG Pledges Investment in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The International Digital
Group (IDG) of the United States has announced it will invest
one-billion yuan (120 million U.S. dollars) over the next five
years in Shenzhen, the special economic zone in south China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
This money will be focused on high-technology including 36
million U.S. dollars for digital communications, 36 million for
computer software, 24 million for genetic engineering, and 24
million for electronic components.
</P>
<P>
The IDG began investing in Shenzhen in February, and has set up
four firms since then. It also has pledged to inject another 60
million yuan (7.25 million US dollars) of investment in the latter
half of this year.
</P>
<P>
As the first special economic zone in China, Shenzhen is home
to a great many high-tech companies. The zone also has a stock
market which provides favorable conditions for venture capital
investment, according to an IDG spokesman.  
</P>
</TEXT>
