<HEADLINE> Ecuador's Banana Exports to Asia Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's banana exports fell
in the first eight months of this year, because of the Asian
financial crisis, official statistics showed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's total banana exports dropped 18.7 percent, from 143
million boxes to 117 million boxes, compared to the same period in
1997.
</P>
<P>
But the amount of exports to the China between January and June
of 1998 dropped 78 percent, from 35.8 million U.S. dollars to 7.9
million dollars over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In South Korea, the volume fell 99 percent, from 3.3 million
dollars to less than 42,000 dollars, and in Japan, 18 percent
less, according to the National Banana Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador sent 400,000 tons of bananas to Asia last year, 10
percent of the fruit's total exports. However, the number will
reduce to 300,000 tons by the end of 1998, which means a
50-million-dollar loss to Ecuador, it said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in Russia, Ecuador dropped 20 percent in its banana
exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
