<HEADLINE> High Temperatures Hover Over Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- High temperatures have
hovered over the Chinese capital for the past week, causing some
problems for Beijingers.
</P>
<P>
Some people have begun using their air conditioners again after
turning them off nearly a month ago, and buses equipped with air
conditioning are again top choice of commuters.
</P>
<P>
Bicycle riders are dripping with sweat and some people are
fainting in the scorching heat.
</P>
<P>
The temperature remained over 30 degrees Celsius all last week,
with the high reaching 31.5 degrees on September 6.
</P>
<P>
According to the Beijing Municipal Meteorological Station, high
temperatures in September were seldom recorded in the past. The
cause of unusually hot weather is believed to be the combination
of strong continental hot air pressure over Beijing and a dearth
of cooler air. Clear weather is also a factor contributing to the
high temperature in the city.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists predicts that high temperatures will continue
for another week, with highs exceeding 30 degrees Celsius.
</P>
<P>
Cooler air is expected to arrive by late September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
