<HEADLINE> Austria Welcomes Nomination of Primakov </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Austria on Thursday welcomed
the nomination of Yevgeny Primakov as prime minister of Russia
as a move to return stability to the economically stricken country.
</P>
<P>
"Austria welcomes every step that can lead Russia to an early
realization of stability," Austrian Chancellor Viktor Klima said.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin nominated Acting
Foreign Minister Primakov for the premiership after the lower
house of parliament, the State Duma, twice rejected his first
choice, Acting Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
Klima said it was of upmost importance for Russia to establish
a government capable of acting and from this point of view,
Yeltsin's compromise was creditable.
</P>
<P>
He added that as soon as Russia had a government, a European
Union delegation would go to Moscow for talks on economic aid.
</P>
<P>
The delegation would consist of the EU foreign ministers of
Austria, Britain and Germany and Austrian Finance Minister and
chairman of the EU committee of finance ministers Rudolf
Edlinger. Austria now holds the rotating EU presidency.
</P>
<P>
Klima said Russia's troubles went beyond an economic crisis to
become a constitutional crisis and the state must find "a reform
road that can accompany social harmony".
</P>
<P>
Austrian Foreign Minister Wolfgang Schoessel also welcomed the
nomination of Primakov, noting that Primakov, for years, had
"built Russia's image" in the world and remained "a stable
element" in Russian policies.
</P>
<P>
Schoessel, also vice chancellor of Austria, stressed that
Russia needed a continuous and stable policy and Vienna would
support a Russian government that "continues to uphold democracy
and adheres to the reform path". 
</P>
</TEXT>
