<HEADLINE> France Bans Takeoff, Landing of Yugoslav Airlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 10 (Xinhua) -- France started to enforce a
European Union ban on the takeoff and landing of Yugoslav airline
JAT planes on midnight Thursday in protest against the growing
tension in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret
announced that the last JAT flight had left Paris and the ban
would not apply to emergency landings and takeoffs or JAT planes
flying through French air space.
</P>
<P>
She said France was implementing an EU decision on September 7
to impose sanctions on Yugoslavia for its use of violence in
Kosovo against the majority ethnic Albanians there.
</P>
<P>
French airlines are continuing flights between Paris and
Belgrade as Yugoslavia has not taken reciprocal measures. 
