<HEADLINE> New Zhejiang University Set to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 11 ( Xinhua ) -- New Zhejiang University,
an incorporation of four universities, will open its doors for the
first time on September 15.
</P>
<P>
Located in Hangzhou, capital of east China's Zhejiang Province,
the new university is made up of four previously separate
universities -- Zhejiang University, Hangzhou University, Zhejiang
Agricultural University and Zhejiang Medical Sciences University.
</P>
<P>
According to the preparatory committee, the new university will
be under unified management for personnel, finance, teaching and
scientific research.
</P>
<P>
The committee said New Zhejiang University will offer 13
two-year majors, 145 four-year majors, 192 master's degree majors,
124 doctorate specialities, and 12 post-doctorate specialities.
</P>
<P>
The university also boasts 13 state key educational
departments, ten state key laboratories, and four state
engineering research and technology centers.
</P>
<P>
The university will gradually absorb the credit system from the
former school-year system.
</P>
<P>
The committee said the newly established university will create
a computer network enabling the four former universities to share
their educational resources and exchange information. 
</P>
</TEXT>
