<HEADLINE> 11 Killed in Bus Collision in Indramayu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A total of 11 people were
killed and 38 others injured in two public buses which collided in
Indramayu district, 240 kilometers east of Jakarta, on Wednesday
night, national newspapers reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The collision occurred after the "Garuda Mas" which was coming
from Jakarta, attempted to overtake another vehicle, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
As the "Garuda Mas" driver steered the bus to the right, he
suddenly saw some of the bridge's pillars in front of him. And to
avoid them, he swerved into the lane reserved for vehicles going
in opposite direction.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the public bus "Ismo" was approaching from
the other direction and the inevitable happened: the two buses ran
into each other head on.
</P>
<P>
The impact pushed the "Ismo" off the bridge and into the river,
followed by the "Garuda Mas" which fell on "Ismo"'s top, the
report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
