<HEADLINE> First Six Hall of Fame Players Named </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The first six players which
will be put into the new English Premier League Hall of Fame were
named on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The six players are Peter Schmeichel, Eric Cantona, Alan
Shearer, Les Ferdinand, Gianfranco Zola and Dennis Bergkamp.
</P>
<P>
The players were selected for their overall performance in
each of the first six seasons of the league, which began in the
1992-93 season.
</P>
<P>
Sir Geoff Hurst, the chairman of the 19-strong panel of
experts who selected the players said at the Hall of Fame's
launch: "One thing we looked for was excitement which got us up
out of our seats."
</P>
<P>
Questioned about the fact that only two English players were
selected, Shearer and Ferdinand, Sir Geoff said: "I don't think
we have produced enough top class English players recently, but
players like Michael Owen and Rio Ferdinand might be included if
you turn the clock forward six years."
</P>
<P>
The next six players will be inducted after a vote by fans but
the date of the next induction has not yet been fixed. The Hall
of Fame will open in London next spring.
</P>
<P>
The players were elected for their performances in the
following seasons:
</P>
<P>
1992-93 Peter Scheimchel (Manchester United, Denmark)
</P>
<P>
1993-94 Eric Cantona (Manchester United, France)
</P>
<P>
1994-95 Alan Shearer (Blackburn Rovers, England)
</P>
<P>
1995-96 Les Ferdinand (Newcastle United, England)
</P>
<P>
1996-97 Gianfranco Zola (Chelsea, Italy)
</P>
<P>
1997-98 Dennis Bergkamp (Arsenal, Netherlands)
</P>
