<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Commissioner Visits Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu Thursday met with European Union (EU) Commissioner
Hans van den Broek, who ended his two-day official visit to
Romania.
</P>
<P>
Issues were approached such as Romania's Partnership for EU
accession and the integration process speeding-up.
</P>
<P>
Hans van den Broek is the EU commissioner in charge of
relations with countries in central and eastern Europe as well as
of EU foreign policy and joint security. The purpose of his visit
is to reassert the EU's pledge to support Romania in its efforts
for EU accession, as well as to inspect the current stage of the
country's preparations in this direction.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Hans van den Broek met with Prime Minister
Radu Vasile, Senate President Petre Roman and Speaker of the
Chamber of Deputies Ion Diaconescu. On the occasion, the European
Commission's high official voiced worry about Romania's chances of
integration in the European structures, because of the country's
economic decline. He said right now Romania should speed up the
reform and the privatization process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
