<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Emergency Disaster Aid to Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Thursday
approved a 369 million U.S. dollar loan for an emergency flood and
earthquake recovery project loan to assist Turkey in its
post-disaster reconstruction efforts.
</P>
<P>
The project will help restore basic infrastructure in
municipalities and rural areas affected by the flood, provide
assistance to restore housing in the earthquake-affected province
of Adana and reduce vulnerability to future floods and
earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
After Turkey joined the World Bank in 1947, bank commitments to
the country total some 26.88 billion dollars for 133 projects.
</P>
