<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Okays 20 Mln Dlr Credit for Gambia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 10 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Thursday
okayed an interest-free credit of 20 million U.S. dollars to
Gambia to finance wide-ranging improvements in education.
</P>
<P>
Over the next 8 years, the Gambian government's Third
Education Sector Program will promote sector-wide development,
from primary through university and technical education. There
will be a special emphasis on girls' education and on improving
management and capacity.
</P>
<P>
The program will be financed through one of the World Bank's
new flexible lending instruments, the Adaptable Program Lending
credit. The credit will be used to finance the first of two
four-year phases of the program and be channeled through the
International Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's
concessional lending affiliate for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
